          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "options",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "A dictionary of options affecting the level of detail of the physics shape, or "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "nil"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " to use default options. For applicable keys and their possible values, see "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "Shape Creation Options Keys"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "return_value",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Return Value",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A new physics shape object."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If you create a physics shape using one of the basic geometry classes ("
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnbox"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnsphere"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnpyramid"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scncone"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scncylinder"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", or "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scncapsule"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "), SceneKit uses an idealized form of that geometry for the physics shape instead of using the geometryâ€™s vertex data to simulate collisions. For example, if you create a physics shape from an "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnsphere"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object, SceneKit simulates collisions for any object that passes within the sphereâ€™s radius. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Because the idealized forms of simple geometries are computationally much simpler than the vertex data needed for displaying them, using basic geometries for physics shapes (or compound shapes created from basic geometries with the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnphysicsshape/1508886-shapewithshapes"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method) often provides the best balance between simulation accuracy and performance. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To use the newly created physics shape, create a physics body with the the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnphysicsbody/1514797-bodywithtype"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method, or assign the shape to the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnphysicsbody/1514789-physicsshape"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property of an existing body."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
